<HEAD>Army Reported to Kill 300 Uganda Rebels in Surprise Raid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAMPALA, Uganda (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In a surprise attack on a rebel camp,
government troops killed at least 300 insurgents and captured 500, a
newspaper reported.
   The reported assault would be one of the government's most
successful blows against the 2-year-old insurgency of the Uganda
People's Army.
   The army attacked the camp near Sorito, about 220 miles northeast
of Kampala, and battled about 1,500 defenders for almost two hours
Saturday, the Munno daily reported.
