<HEAD>Bomb Explodes Under Police Car, Fourth Attack This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded today under a
police car parked at a black policemen's barracks, but no injuries
were reported.
   It was the fourth attack on police since Sunday, but so far the
only injuries have been to a 14-year-old boy and three other
civilians hurt when a bomb exploded Sunday under a car at Duduza
Soccer Stadium in a black township.
   Police have not said who they believe is responsible for the
attacks.
   Most bombings are blamed on the outlawed African National
Congress, which has been waging a sabotage and bombing campaign to
force an end to white control of the government.
   Police said the latest bomb went off at 2:15 a.m. under a car
parked in front of the Sandton suburban barracks north of
Johannesburg.
