<SECOND>PM-Chickens Hatched,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>Chicken Joke Comes Home To Roost</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The chicks that appeared on the boss'
desk didn't come from the eggs he'd accidentally left behind, but
rather from the fertile imaginations of office practical jokers.
   Dave Brosman, assistant director of the Albuquerque Public Works
Department, left cartons of eggs on his desk over a four-day
weekend. When he returned on Tuesday, he found two chicks scratching
around on his desk.
   His secretary, Marian Peterson, told him she found the chicks
hatched when she came to work, and she repeated the story to an
Albuquerque newspaper Tuesday.
   But it turns out Peterson hatched the plot with co-worker and egg
dealer Gary Daves, who brought the chicks to work.
   ``It was entertainment that turned larger than life,'' Daves
said. ``Blame it on the silliness of June.''
   Brosman said he really believed the chicks had hatched from the
eggs.
   ``It was a joke that went too far, but it did lighten up the
day,'' he said.
</TEXT>
