<FIRST>r a PM-Obit-Stern 1stLd-Writethru a0593 06-15 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Obit-Stern, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0593,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>Designer of Ritz Crackers Box Dead at 99</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: CORRECTS lead and 3rd graf pvs, `His projects ...' to show that
he redesigned Animal Crackers box.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sydney S. Stern, designer of the
original Ritz Crackers box, has died at age 99.
   The artist died of heart failure June 5 at Palms of Pasadena
Hospital.
   Stern, who retired to Seminole from New York City in 1956, went
to work in 1923 for the National Biscuit Co., where he designed
cartoons, wrappers and boxes.
   His projects included redesigning Nabisco's Animal Crackers box,
which depicts caged lions, tigers and bears in bright colors. Stern
also put the cracker on the Uneeda biscuit box and helped design the
Shredded Wheat Box.
   Stern studied at New York's Art Students League, Columbia
University and the Pennsylvania Academy of Fine Arts.
   The Beaux Arts Gallery plans an Oct. 4 exhibit of his works on
the 100th anniversary of his birth, said Tom Reese, gallery director.
   Survivors include three sons; two brothers; four grandchildren
and a great-grandchild.
</TEXT>
