<HEAD>Omani Tribesman Strikes Gold, But Wants Water</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUSCAT, Oman (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Omani tribesman who struck gold while
digging a well said he would continue looking for water, a newspaper
reported Thursday.
   Rashid Nassri was hunting for water with his brother when he
unearthed gold deposits 70 feet down, the newspaper Oman quoted
relatives as saying.
   He handed his samples to the tribal sheik of Ibri, a desert plain
200 miles west of Muscat, saying he was not interested in it, the
family said.
   Relatives quoted Nassri, 35, as saying: ``What will I do with the
gold? For me, water is more precious than this glittering metal.''
   Government mineral officials were analyzing the find.
   Nassri continued his search for water, the Arabic-language
newspaper said.
