<FIRST>r a AM-BrushFire     06-15 0158</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Brush Fire,0160</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wind-Whipped Blazes Signals Fire Season In California</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN MARTIN, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A wind-whipped brush fire charred more
than 375 acres and destroyed two houses, a trailer and six other
structures before being contained.
   ``Fire season is definitely here,'' said Chris Morgan, spokesman
for the California Department of Forestry, urging Northern
California residents to take extra care to trim shrubs and grass
around their homes for fire protection.
   His agency had no damage estimate for the single-family homes
that were lost in Wednesday's fire southeast of San Francisco.
Officials did not know if the trailer served as a home. The
remaining structures were believed to have been sheds and other
types of storage facilities.
   Morgan said gusty afternoon wind was a major obstacle to
controlling the fire, but it was declared contained after about 4{
hours of work by more than 50 firefighters, 16 fire engines, a
bulldozer, a helicopter and three air tankers.
</TEXT>
