<HEAD>France To Drop Visa Requirement for U.S. Visitors</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   France has agreed to drop its visa requirement
for U.S. citizens who travel to that country for visits of 90 days
on either business or pleasure trips, the State Department said
Thursday.
   The new policy will take effect July 1.
   The State Department announced recently that France is among a
small group of countries for which the United States no longer
requires visas for most categories of travelers.
