<HEAD>Oil Tanker Grounded Off Virginia Beach ^Eds: UPDATES throughout to
CORRECT that tanker was carrying 8 million gallons sted 200,000 and CORRECT
destination. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTSMOUTH, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tanker carrying 8 million gallons of oil
ran aground off Virginia Beach, but the Coast Guard today said there
was no spill.
   Divers determined the hull was intact, said Coast Guard spokesman
Steve Blando.
   Blando said the Omi Leader ran aground on a sandy shoal six miles
off Cape Henry after 9 p.m. Wednesday.
   Tugboats were unable to free the tanker, and the Coast Guard
began pumping out 1.6 million gallons to lighten the vessel and
refloat it, said Petty Officer 1st Class Rick Woods.
   ``There are no traces of any damage to the vessel, no spill
outside of the vessel,'' he said.
   Blando said the U.S.-registered tanker was en route to Koch
Refinery in Newport News when it went aground.
   The cause of the accident was under investigation.
