<SECOND>BC-House S&amp;L-Hyde Roll Call, 3 Takes,</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 326-94 roll call Thursday by which
the House rejected an amendment by Rep. Henry Hyde, R-Ill., to
President Bush's savings and loan bailout proposal.
   The amendment would have provided a mechanism for exempting 241
of the nation's 2,938 S&amp;Ls from having to raise $6 billion of new
capital as a buffer between risky loans and federal deposit
insurance funds.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote in favor of the exemptions.
   Voting yes were 38 Democrats and 56 Republicans.
   Voting no were 212 Democrats and 114 Republicans.
   Y is yes. N is no. X denotes those not voting. Present denotes
those who voted they were ``present'' at the time of the vote but
did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There is 1 vacancy in the 435-member House.
</TEXT>
