<FIRST>r w AM-GeneticTomato     06-15 0088</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Genetic Tomato,90</SECOND>
<HEAD>USDA: Tests Good on Caterpillar-proof Tomato</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Agriculture Department said Thursday it has
found no significant environmental impact from field trials of
tomatoes engineered genetically to resist insects.
   The Monsanto Co., Chesterfield, Mo., is conducting the field test
in Hughson, Calif., the department's Animal and Plant Health
Inspection Service said.
   Scientists used a delta endotoxin gene found naturally in the
bacteria, Bacillus thuringiensis, which is toxic to certain
destructive caterpillars. Monsanto is also testing the experimental
tomatoes in Florida and Illinois.
