$100 billion of savings and loan losses.
   As the House began debate on the measure Wednesday, Bush joined
the campaign against industry-sponsored amendments by Reps. Jimmy
Quillen, R-Tenn., and Henry Hyde, R-Ill., to exempt about 450 S&amp;Ls
from having to put up $6 billion in new capital to protect taxpayers
from future losses.
</TEXT>
