<TEXT>
   The outlook for U.S. advertising spending has
brightened in the past six months and is now expected to rise 6.9
percent this year, one of the industry's most widely-followed
forecasts said.
   Robert Coen, director of forecasting for the ad agency
McCann-Erickson, said Wednesday that 1989 growth should exceed the
6.1 percent rise he projected last December because national
advertiser spending has exceeded his expectations and the economic
climate has improved.
</TEXT>
