<FIRST>r f BC-WheelabratorMerger     06-15 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Wheelabrator Merger,0180</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wheelabrator, Majority Shareholder Merge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMPTON, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wheelabrator Technologies Inc., whose
facilities generate electricity by burning trash, said today it will
merger with Wheelabrator Group Inc. to create a $1.3 billion energy
and recycling company.
   The combined company will be named Wheelabrator Technologies
Inc., according to a news release issued by Wheelabrator Group,
which is Wheelabrator Technology's largest shareholder.
   The transaction is subject to approval of shareholders in both
companies.
   ``The merger will enhance the financial capabilities of
Wheelabrator and offer investors a greater opportunity to
participate in its rapid growth,'' said Paul M. Montrone, chairman
and chief executive officer of Wheelabrator Technologies. He will
head the new company.
   The new company will apply for its stock to trade on the New York
Stock Exchange, while Wheelabrator Group stock will be delisted from
the Nasdaq National Market System.
   Wheelabrator Technologies' revenues last year were $1.2 billion.
The company operates 10 waste-to-energy plants and is building four
more. The company has 17 similar projects in earlier stages of
development.
</TEXT>
