<FIRST>u f PM-Thermos-Japan     06-15 0287</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Thermos-Japan,0297</SECOND>
<HEAD>Japanese Firm Buying Thermos Co.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PROSPECT HEIGHTS, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The parent company of Thermos Co.
today announced the sale of the famous maker of vacuum bottles to
Japanese manufacturer Nippon Sanso K.K. for an undisclosed sum.
   Household International Inc., based in Prospect Heights, said in
a news release that it expects to complete the cash transaction by
the end of August.
   Thermos, based in Freeport, Ill., is the largest of six
manufacturing subsidiaries that Household is selling as part of its
decision to focus on the financial services businesses, which
include Household Finance Corp.
   Thermos, established in 1907, is a leader in the design,
manufacturing and marketing of outdoor leisure products in North
America and Europe. It is best known for commercialization of the
glass vacuum bottle. The company also makes lunch boxes and
recreational products.
   The company employs about 1,900 people in the United States,
Canada and England. It had sales of about $194 million in 1988.
   Nippon Sanso is one of the world's largest manufacturers of
industrial gas, including oxygen, nitrogen and argon. It has
recently diversified into consumer products such as frozen foods and
stainless steel vacuum bottles, and its acquisition of Thermos
represents a further expansion in the consumer-products area.
   Household announced in January plans to divest all manufacturing
operations. In April it spun off to shareholders three manufacturing
companies: Eljer Industries Inc., Scotsman Industries Inc. and
Schwitzer Inc.
   Household expects to sell its five remaining manufacturing
companies by the end of the summer, said spokesman Robert Hartney.
Those companies are: GC-Thorsen, Albion Industries, King-Sealy, Omni
Products International and WaterTest Corp.
   Household's financial-services businesses are Household Finance,
Household Bank, Household Commercial Finance and the Alexander
Hamilton Life Insurance Co.
</TEXT>
