<SECOND>BC-Auto Recalls,0135</SECOND>
<HEAD>GM Recalls Chevy, GMC Bus, Truck Chassis; Pickups with Trailer Hitches</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Motors Corp. on Thursday recalled about
21,500 1986-89 Chevrolet and GMC school bus chassis and about 6,000
1989 Chevrolet and GMC full-size pickups with optional trailer
hitches.
   The company said a crack could develop in its B6- and S7-model
school bus chassis next to a weld on the fuel tank. The crack could
cause a fuel leak.
   Trailer hitches on the full-size pickups with 8-foot cargo boxes
may have been tightened improperly when installed, possibly
resulting in bolt breakage.
   GM said it would inspect vehicles in both recalls and replace
parts where needed for free.
   The company said it was unaware of any accidents or injuries due
to either problem.
</TEXT>
