   Analysts detected little reaction to a Commerce Department report
showing the country's merchandise trade deficit fell to $8.26
billion in April.
   The improvement in the trade balance was largely expected but
economists are doubtful the deficit will continue to shrink due to
the strength of the dollar, which makes American exports more
expensive for foreign buyers.
   Takeover stocks continued to figure on the list of actively
traded NYSE-listed issues.
   Warner Communications was the most heavily traded stock on volume
of 1.6 million shares and was up 1{ to 56{. Paramount
Communications, the second most heavily traded stock, rose { to 60
while Time gained 3[ to 172.
   Monsanto rose 3 to 107 in active trading. The company announced
settlement of a dispute involving an intrauterine device.
</TEXT>
