<FIRST>r f BC-AutoProdn     06-15 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0152</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
228,888 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
231,458, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
when 255,207 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 141,151 cars this week,
compared with 143,501 a week ago and 168,088 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 87,737,
compared with last week's 87,957 and last year's 87,119.
   Canadian automakers were to build 24,497 cars this week, up from
18,922 a week ago but down from last year's 24,730.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,622, compared
with 18,266 a week ago and 20,497 in the same week last year.
