   The NYSE composite index of all its listed common stocks slid
1.74 to 179.09.
   A downturn in bond prices spilled over into the stock market,
analysts said. Today's weakness in the credit market, which recently
has rallied on rising optimism that a robust dollar would attract
foreign investors, coincided with a decline in the dollar.
   Wall Street analysts also said trading maneuvers related to
stock-index futures contributed to the selloff. Stocks are being
sold ahead of Friday's ``triple witching hour'' when stock-index
futures, index options and options on individual stocks expire.
