<SECOND>BC-WPP-Ogilvy,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>WPP Shareholders Approve Ogilvy Buyout</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shareholders of WPP Group PLC unanimously
approved on Thursday the advertising company's proposed $864 million
acquisition of Ogilvy Group Inc. in what would be the biggest
takeover in the ad business.
   The decision, which came at a shareholders meeting in London, had
been expected. Ogilvy, based in New York, and WPP agreed on the
buyout May 16.
   The vote removes one of the final hurdles to the deal that would
make WPP Group the second largest advertising conglomerate in the
world, trailing only Saatchi &amp; Saatchi PLC. Both WPP and Saatchi are
based in London.
   The deal also depends on regulatory approval and the tender of at
least two-thirds of Ogilvy's 16 million shares by the deadline of
12:01 a.m. EDT Friday.
