<FIRST>s f BC-EasternChronology Adv18   06-15 0355</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Eastern Chronology, Adv 18,0376</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv18</HEAD>
<HEAD>For release Sunday June 18 and thereafter.</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Eastern-Maintenance</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are key events in the strike against Eastern Airlines:
   _Feb. 1 _ Eastern rejects binding arbitration offer by National
Mediation Board, which declares a 30-day cooling-off period between
Machinists and the company.
   _Feb. 15 _ More than 97 percent of the 8,500 Machinists authorize
a strike. Pilots indicate they will side with the Machinists.
   _March 3 _ President Bush declines to use his authority to
postpone a strike. Machinists reject latest contract offer.
   _March 4 _ Strike begins, honored by pilots and flight
attendants, forcing airline to cancel most flights.
   _March 6 _ Eastern idles 7,000 non-union workers.
   _March 9 _ Eastern files for protection from creditors under
Chapter 11 in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in New York.
   _March 30 _ A group led by Baseball Commissioner Peter Ueberroth
says it submitted and withdrew a $464 million buyout proposal for
Eastern.
   _March 31 _ Property developer Donald Trump completes
restructured deal to buy Eastern's Northeast shuttle for $365
million.
   _April 4 _ Ueberroth's group makes a new offer to purchase
Eastern.
   _April 6 _ Texas Air announces the Ueberroth group will acquire
Eastern and a stake in the System One reservations system in a deal
valued at $464 million. Employees would own part of the airline in
return for concessions.
   _April 12 _ Ueberroth deal collapses over dispute on who will run
Eastern until his group can take control. Eastern announces plan to
reorganize as a smaller carrier.
   _May 3 _ U.S. Bankruptcy Judge Burton R. Lifland asks interested
bidders to submit offers for Eastern. Several groups begin to
express interest.
   _May 23 _ Eastern graduates its first class of new pilot hired
since the start of the strike.
   _May 25 _ Lifland formally approves the sale of the shuttle to
Trump for $365 million.
   _June 2 _ Eastern announces an austerity program for non-union
employees designed to help it rebuild from bankruptcy.
   _June 5 _ Lifland directs Eastern and creditors to start
negotiations on a bankruptcy reorganization plan.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End adv for Sunday June 18</NOTE>
</DOC>
