<FIRST>s f BC-Eastern-Glance Adv18   06-15 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Eastern-Glance, Adv 18,0208</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv18</HEAD>
<HEAD>For release Sunday June 18 and thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eastern Before and After Proposed Downsizing</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Eastern-Maintenance</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a look at Eastern Airlines before the strike that started
March 4, compared with management's proposed plan to sharply reduce
the carrier's size and sell $1.8 billion in assets. Eastern is under
Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection and the management plan must be
approved by creditors and a federal bankruptcy judge.
   --- Owner: The 60-year-old airline has been owned by Texas Air
Corp., headed by Chairman Frank Lorenzo, since 1986.
   Headquarters: Miami. Lorenzo has hinted it might be moved under
the proposed streamlining plan. A possible new location would be
Atlanta.
   Employees: Before strike: 31,200, including 3,600 pilots. Under
plan: 17,000, including 1,700 pilots.
   Size of fleet: Before strike: 255 jets. Under plan: 157.
   Cities served: Before strike: 102, with major markets in South
Florida, the Caribbean, East Coast and Latin America. Under plan:
77, unspecified.
   Number of daily scheduled flight hours: Before strike, 2,076.
Under plan, 1,473.
   Passengers: Before strike, 100,000 average daily. Under plan,
unknown.
   Target date for emergence from Chapter 11: September 1989.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End adv for Sunday June 18</NOTE>
</DOC>
